10 (b) (1) (i) The Corporation shall provide loans up to $250,000 to finance the
11 costs of eligible seafood processing projects in accordance with this section, including
12 historic oyster shucking facilities, not to exceed $25,000 for each full–time job or [$10,000
13 for each] seasonal full–time job that is projected to be created or retained.
14 (ii) Beginning 1 year after receipt of a loan under this section, a loan
15 recipient shall report each year for 3 consecutive years to the Corporation to certify the
16 number of full–time jobs and seasonal full–time jobs that were created or retained by the
17 recipient during the previous 12–month period.
18 (2) Financing provided under this section shall be conditioned on the
19 agreement by the recipient to comply with the provisions of § 4–1019.2 of the Natural
20 Resources Article until the loan is repaid.
21 (3) The Corporation shall forgive any loan provided under this section as
22 follows:
23 (i) the current market value as established in § 4–1019.2 of the
24 Natural Resources Article for each bushel of oyster shells that the loan recipient returns to
25 the Department of Natural Resources at no cost; or
26 (ii) $25 for each bushel of spat–on–shell that the person plants on a
27 public fishery bottom as verified by the Department of Natural Resources.
28 (c) A person is eligible to receive financing under this section if the person:
29 (1) (i) has been a licensed seafood dealer for at least [5] 3 years; or
30 (ii) has held a tidal fish license issued under § 4–701 of the Natural
31 Resources Article for at least 5 years and agrees to obtain a seafood dealer license on
32 receiving financing under this section;
33 (2) has paid all applicable business taxes and fees for the past 5 years;

